Hi Maura,
Sergey Efuni, MD, PhD is an Internal Medicine and Clinical Immunology=96tra=
ined physician with over 25 years of global experience spanning academia, i=
ndustry, and clinical research. He is currently Vice President, Global Clin=
ical Development at OncoC4, where he leads late-stage oncology programs inc=
luding a pivotal Phase 3 study in NSCLC across 160+ sites worldwide. Previo=
usly, Sergey held senior leadership roles at Magenta, MorphoSys/Constellati=
on, and Kyowa Kirin, driving development programs across immunology, neurol=
ogy, and rare diseases.
Sergey is particularly interested in roles that pique his professional inte=
rest. Nothing is necessarily "pushing" him out of his role with OncoC4, but=
 he is the type of person that likes to challenge himself and do difficult =
things. He has been in a few unfortunate situations with Constellation and =
Magenta, being forced out through acquisitions, so he is looking for a long=
 term opportunity, mirroring his tenure at Kyowa Kirin. He is based in New =
Hope, PA and is willing to relocate to Cambridge, MA for the right opportun=
ity. He values working onsite and prefers a hybrid model. He is targeting a=
 base salary of $410k - $420k. He understands relocation would need to occu=
r within 90 days or less of starting and $20k would be the max given toward=
s relocation costs if given at all.
Sergey Efuni, MD, PhD

  *
Vice President, Global Clinical Development at OncoC4 Inc
  *
MD in Internal Medicine from Moscow Medical Academy, and PhD in Immunology =
from Institute of Immunology
  *
25+ years of global clinical development experience across academia, biotec=
h, and pharma
  *
FDA/EMA-approved programs: Nourianz, Poteligeo, Pelabresib
  *
Leadership experience managing cross-functional teams of 50+ across the US,=
 Japan, and Europe
  *
Therapeutic expertise: oncology, immunology, neurology, gastroenterology, a=
nd rare diseases



